          <msContents>
            <summary>Manual with associated rules and laws (dharma) connected to a special fast (vrata) for women who desire to avoid widowhood. Selection from a larger compendium of observances (vratas) thought to be drawn primarily from the Skanda Purāṇa, a text that the manuscript refers to (f. 29v).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Sāvitrīvrata</title>
              <title type="vernacular">सावित्रीव्रत</title>
              <author>
                <persName type="authority">Śaṅkarabhaṭṭa (Son of Nīlakaṇṭha)</persName>
              </author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti vratārke skāṃde so[?]āyanaṃ sāvitrīvratam saṃpūrṇa śrīrastu // (f. 29r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
